# CIVITASWATCH SYSTEM BLUEPRINT

## Core Entity & Architecture Model (MVP Foundation)

---

# 1. PURPOSE

This document defines the **core data model and system architecture** for CivitasWatch.

It ensures:

* consistency across modules
* scalability across sectors
* clean separation between operations and intelligence
* ability to link people, vehicles, places, and incidents

This is the **foundation layer** — all future features must align with this.

---

# 2. CORE DESIGN PRINCIPLES

## 2.1 One Real-World Thing = One Record

* One person = one Person record
* One vehicle = one Vehicle record
* One place = one Place record

No duplication.

---

## 2.2 Link Everything (Do Not Embed Everything)

Use relationships instead of duplication:

* Incident ↔ Person
* Incident ↔ Vehicle
* Incident ↔ Place
* Patrol ↔ Events

---

## 2.3 Separate Operations from Intelligence

* Operational data = visible to patrol/admin
* Intelligence data = restricted access

---

## 2.4 Role-Based Visibility

Different users see different layers:

* Patroller
* Control Room
* Admin
* Intelligence

---

# 3. CORE ENTITIES

---

## 3.1 Person

Represents any human in the system.

**Used for:**

* resident
* patroller
* witness
* victim
* suspect
* person of interest

**Fields:**

* id
* firstName
* lastName
* phonePrimary
* phoneSecondary
* idNumber (optional)
* dateOfBirth (optional)
* gender (optional)
* notes
* status (active/inactive)
* createdAt
* updatedAt

---

## 3.2 Resident

Linked to Person (NOT separate duplicate data).

**Fields:**

* id
* personId
* addressId (placeId)
* sectorId
* residentType (resident/business/caretaker/etc)
* emergencyContactName
* emergencyContactPhone
* isKeyholder
* isVulnerable
* notes
* status

---

## 3.3 User (System Login)

Authentication layer.

**Fields:**

* id
* personId
* email
* passwordHash
* role
* isActive
* lastLoginAt

---

## 3.4 PatrollerProfile

Operational identity of patroller.

**Fields:**

* id
* personId
* callSign
* radioNumber (optional)
* employmentType
* status
* joinedAt
* notes

---

## 3.5 Vehicle

Patrol + observed vehicles.

**Fields:**

* id
* registration
* make
* model
* type
* colour
* ownershipType
* status
* notes

---

## 3.6 Place

Universal location entity.

**Used for:**

* addresses
* incidents
* checkpoints
* hotspots

**Fields:**

* id
* name
* addressLine1
* addressLine2
* suburb
* city
* sectorId
* latitude
* longitude
* placeType
* notes

---

## 3.7 Sector

Operational boundary.

**Fields:**

* id
* name
* code
* description
* parentSectorId
* isActive

---

## 3.8 PatrolSession

Active patrol lifecycle.

**Fields:**

* id
* userId
* vehicleId
* sectorId
* checklistId
* startTime
* endTime
* startKm
* endKm
* totalKm
* summary
* status

---

## 3.9 PatrolEvent

Logs actions during patrol.

**Fields:**

* id
* patrolId
* eventType (STAND_DOWN, RESUME, etc)
* incidentId (optional)
* infrastructureReportId (optional)
* description
* assistanceType
* sceneActive
* createdAt

---

## 3.10 Incident

Core operational event.

**Fields:**

* id
* incidentCode
* title
* description
* placeId
* sectorId
* reportedAt
* occurredAt
* status
* severity
* source
* createdByUserId
* linkedPatrolId

---

## 3.11 IncidentPersonLink

Connects people to incidents.

**Fields:**

* id
* incidentId
* personId
* roleInIncident (witness/victim/suspect/etc)
* notes

---

## 3.12 IncidentVehicleLink

Connects vehicles to incidents.

**Fields:**

* id
* incidentId
* vehicleId (optional)
* externalRegistration
* externalMake
* externalColour
* roleInIncident
* notes

---

## 3.13 InterestFlag (INTELLIGENCE LAYER)

Used for POI / VOI / Place of Interest.

**Fields:**

* id
* entityType (PERSON / VEHICLE / PLACE)
* entityId
* flagType
* reason
* riskLevel
* createdByUserId
* restrictedLevel
* active
* createdAt

---

## 3.14 InfrastructureReport

Operational issue tracking.

**Fields:**

* id
* patrolId
* reportedByUserId
* placeId
* sectorId
* category
* description
* severity
* status
* reportedAt
* resolvedAt

---

## 3.15 Attachment

Shared media storage.

**Fields:**

* id
* entityType
* entityId
* fileUrl
* fileType
* caption
* uploadedByUserId
* classification
* createdAt

---

## 3.16 Checklist

Operational compliance.

**Fields:**

* id
* checklistType
* userId
* vehicleId
* completedAt
* notes

---

# 4. RELATIONSHIPS

* Person ↔ Resident
* Person ↔ User
* Person ↔ PatrollerProfile
* Incident ↔ Person (via link table)
* Incident ↔ Vehicle
* Incident ↔ Place
* PatrolSession ↔ PatrolEvent
* PatrolEvent ↔ Incident
* PatrolEvent ↔ InfrastructureReport

---

# 5. ACCESS MODEL

## Patroller

* Patrol operations
* Events
* Basic resident info

## Control Room

* Active patrols
* Incidents
* Assistance

## Admin

* Reports
* Users
* Vehicles
* Residents

## Intelligence

* Interest flags
* Linked entities
* Restricted data

---

# 6. SYSTEM LAYERS

## Layer 1 — Operational

* Patrols
* Residents
* Incidents
* Infrastructure

## Layer 2 — Reporting

* Patrol reports
* Incident reports
* Patroller activity

## Layer 3 — Intelligence

* POI / VOI / Places of Interest
* Cross-sector linkage
* Pattern analysis

